# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Portfolio SMTP API - Environment Template
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
# This file is a template for local and deployed environment variables.
# It intentionally contains no real credentials.
#
# Usage:
# 1) Copy this file to .env.
# 2) Replace all placeholder values with real values.
# 3) Never commit a real .env file to source control.
#
# Example (PowerShell):
# Copy-Item .env.example .env
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# General Server Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Port used by the local Express API.
# Default in code: 3001
# Must match the frontend proxy configuration.
PORT=3001

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required SMTP Variables (email sending fails without these)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SMTP host name provided by your email provider.
# Examples:
# - smtp.gmail.com
# - smtp.office365.com
# - mail.your-provider.com
SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com

# SMTP port:
# - 587 = STARTTLS (most common)
# - 465 = SSL/TLS (implicit TLS)
SMTP_PORT=587

# SMTP username, usually the full email address.
SMTP_USER=mailer@example.com

# SMTP password or app password.
# Important:
# - Avoid quotes unless the value contains spaces.
# - Never place real secrets in .env.example.
SMTP_PASS=replace_with_secure_password

# Sender address used in the message From header.
# Many providers require this to match SMTP_USER or an approved alias.
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=mailer@example.com

# Recipient address that receives contact form submissions.
SMTP_TO_EMAIL=contact@example.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional SMTP Variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Sender display name visible in email clients.
# Code fallback: "Portfolio Contact"
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Portfolio Contact

# Enables STARTTLS behavior (primarily relevant for port 587).
# Accepted values in code:
# true/false, 1/0, yes/no, y/n, on/off
SMTP_USE_TLS=true

# Enables SSL behavior (typically relevant for port 465).
# For port 465, the code already treats the connection as secure.
SMTP_USE_SSL=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Provider Setup Examples
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Gmail (recommended with app password):
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USE_TLS=true
# SMTP_USE_SSL=false
# SMTP_USER=your.account@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=your_app_password

# Office 365:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.office365.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USE_TLS=true
# SMTP_USE_SSL=false

# Custom mail server with SSL:
# SMTP_HOST=mail.your-domain.tld
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USE_TLS=false
# SMTP_USE_SSL=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Validation and Common Errors
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# If required variables are missing, /api/contact returns:
# "Missing SMTP configuration: ..."
#
# If SMTP authentication fails, /api/contact returns:
# "Failed to send email" plus provider details from Nodemailer.
#
# If form fields are invalid, /api/contact returns one of:
# - Invalid name
# - Invalid email
# - Invalid message
# - Privacy consent is required

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# - Keep .env local, or store values in your hosting secret manager.
# - Never share SMTP_PASS or production mailbox credentials in logs.
# - Prefer app passwords and dedicated mailbox accounts for production.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
